{{PAGENAME}} is a Japanese primordial deity. He was the fourth one to come into existence<ref>https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/umashiashikabihikoji/</ref>
==References==

{{draft}}

{{ill|{{PAGENAME}}|ja|ウマシアシカビヒコヂ}} is a Japanese primordial deity. He was the fourth one to come into existence<ref>https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/umashiashikabihikoji/</ref>
==References==

{{draft}}
[[File:Creation_myths_of_Japan-eng.svg|frame]]
{{ill|{{PAGENAME}}|ja|ウマシアシカビヒコヂ}} is a Japanese primordial deity. He was the fourth one to come into existence<ref>https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/umashiashikabihikoji/</ref> He is one of the five [[Kotoamatsukami]] according to the [[Kojiki]].<ref name=":0">https://archive.ph/LW8jJ</ref>

He is a [[Hitorigami]], or a singular divinity born early in the universe.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2011-05-18 |title=Encyclopedia of Shinto - Home : Concepts of Kami : Hitorigami |url=http://web.archive.org/web/20110518151157/http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=10 |access-date=2023-03-22 |website=web.archive.org}}</ref>

He was not mentioned as an [[Oyagami]] or clan ancestor<ref name=":0" />

